
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gomez-lpwan-fragmentation-header-03.txt'>
    <title>"LPWAN Fragmentation Header", Carles Gomez, Josep Paradells, Jon Crowcroft</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gomez-lpwan-fragmentation-header-03.txt</link>
    <description>LPWAN technologies are characterized by a very limited data unit and/ or payload size, often one order of magnitude below the one in IEEE 802.15.4.  However, many such technologies do not support layer 2 fragmentation.  The 6LoWPAN fragmentation header defined in RFC 4944 represents very high overhead for LPWAN technologies, and it even does not support transporting IPv6 datagrams that require fragmentation over layer 2 technologies of a maximum payload size below 13 bytes.  This specification defines an optimized fragmentation header for LPWAN.</description>
    <dc:date>2016-10-23T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
